<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071139>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33–38. Male genitalia of Isomyia hauwangai sp. nov. 33. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral aspect. 34. Cerci and surstyli, caudal aspect. 35. Aedeagus, left lateral aspect. 36. Aedeagus, from behind. 37. Pregonite and postgonite, left lateral aspect. 38. 5th sternite, ventral aspect. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5071139/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071143>
    dc:description "FIGURES 43–44. Habitus photographs of Isomyia hauwangai sp. nov. (holotype ♂) (length: 9.0–10.0 mm). 43. Dorsal aspect. 44. Lateral aspect." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5071143/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071165>
    dc:description "FIGURES 99–104. Distributions of Namibian Calliphoridae species. 99. Isomyia hauwangai sp. nov. 100. I. natalensis (Villeneuve). 101. I. tristis (Bigot). 102. Zumba antennalis (Villeneuve). 103. Perisiella anchora (Wiedemann). 104. Pseudorhyncomyia braunsi (Villeneuve)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5071165/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

